1
00:00:36,750 --> 00:00:41,708
♪♪♪

2
00:00:44,625 --> 00:00:47,083
[BREAKERS]
Go Breakers!

3
00:00:47,916 --> 00:00:50,458
That's good.
Take a break everyone.

4
00:00:50,541 --> 00:00:56,833
[ALL panting]

5
00:00:56,916 --> 00:00:58,000
[TAKAGI]
You've worked really hard

6
00:00:58,083 --> 00:01:00,500
these past few weeks, gentlemen.

7
00:01:00,583 --> 00:01:01,958
And you've come a long way.

8
00:01:02,041 --> 00:01:04,250
But there's one last
hurdle to cross.

9
00:01:04,333 --> 00:01:05,875
[KAZUMA]
Oh, yeah?

10
00:01:05,958 --> 00:01:08,666
What are you talking about?

11
00:01:12,375 --> 00:01:14,208
[TAKAGI]
Here.

12
00:01:14,291 --> 00:01:16,666
What do our journals
have to do with this?

13
00:01:16,750 --> 00:01:18,125
[TAKAGI]
Everything you need to know

14
00:01:18,208 --> 00:01:20,000
is written inside these books.

15
00:01:20,083 --> 00:01:22,500
I've read every single word
each of you has written down

16
00:01:22,583 --> 00:01:23,708
time and time again.

17
00:01:23,791 --> 00:01:26,541
So, believe me boys.
More than your training.

18
00:01:26,625 --> 00:01:29,916
More than your practice.
More than your routine.

19
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:32,291
This will be your
most important task.

20
00:01:32,375 --> 00:01:34,208
[BOTH gasp]

21
00:01:34,291 --> 00:01:35,333
[TAKAGI]
Pass 'em around.

22
00:01:35,416 --> 00:01:36,541
[HARUKI, KAZUMA]
Uh?

23
00:01:36,625 --> 00:01:39,416
Hold on. Why would we do that?

24
00:01:39,500 --> 00:01:41,875
You guys are gonna read
each other's journals.

25
00:01:41,958 --> 00:01:43,333
[HARUKI, KAZUMA gasping]

26
00:01:43,416 --> 00:01:50,083
[ALL gasping]

27
00:01:50,916 --> 00:01:54,375
[BREAKERS]
Huh?!

28
00:03:37,750 --> 00:03:39,625
Why's everyone so down?

29
00:03:39,708 --> 00:03:42,833
You're not gonna win lookin'
like that, kiddos.

30
00:03:42,916 --> 00:03:45,125
[KAZUMA]
Yeah. You're probably right.

31
00:03:45,208 --> 00:03:46,458
[HARUKI groans]

32
00:03:46,541 --> 00:03:48,166
[CAFE MANAGER 1A]
Are you gonna talk to each other

33
00:03:48,250 --> 00:03:51,166
or just sit there
looking embarrassed?

34
00:03:51,250 --> 00:03:53,041
Your handwriting's adorable.

35
00:03:53,125 --> 00:03:55,291
I had no idea you wrote
in bubble letters.

36
00:03:55,375 --> 00:03:58,416
Be a gentleman and never
mention it again.

37
00:03:58,500 --> 00:04:00,875
Hey Sho, so about your journal.

38
00:04:00,958 --> 00:04:03,708
Uh. Why're there so many
Risujiro stickers?

39
00:04:03,791 --> 00:04:05,958
'Cause Risu's totally awesome.

40
00:04:06,041 --> 00:04:08,833
Hey, Takeru. You write with
such awesome passion!

41
00:04:08,916 --> 00:04:11,458
Ahh! Just kill me now!

42
00:04:11,541 --> 00:04:13,500
[ICHIRO] Ya know what?
This didn't happen!

43
00:04:13,583 --> 00:04:16,291
Let's make a pact to never
speak of this again!

44
00:04:16,375 --> 00:04:17,625
[WATARU]
I concur!

45
00:04:17,708 --> 00:04:22,458
[BREAKERS chattering]

46
00:04:22,541 --> 00:04:25,333
This is the worst...

47
00:04:25,416 --> 00:04:28,250
You guys! Listen!

48
00:04:29,916 --> 00:04:31,583
You know?

49
00:04:31,666 --> 00:04:34,041
I never thought our Cheerleading
Club would make it this far,

50
00:04:34,125 --> 00:04:35,250
but we did.

51
00:04:35,333 --> 00:04:37,125
It began with me and Haru,

52
00:04:37,208 --> 00:04:40,458
and it's gotten bigger
than we ever imagined.

53
00:04:40,541 --> 00:04:44,375
We set out with no experience,
no equipment, heck,

54
00:04:44,458 --> 00:04:49,666
we didn't even have
a coach. Just a dream.

55
00:04:49,750 --> 00:04:52,625
On our first day of practice,
you two couldn't do a handstand.

56
00:04:52,708 --> 00:04:54,875
[WATARU, TON grunt]

57
00:04:54,958 --> 00:04:58,375
[KAZUMA] Then came Ichiro and
Gen, and we got a little better.

58
00:04:58,458 --> 00:04:59,916
And when Sho got involved,

59
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:03,875
we finally started to look
like real cheerleaders.

60
00:05:03,958 --> 00:05:07,083
But we didn't stop
there. No sir.

61
00:05:07,166 --> 00:05:08,750
We performed at
the school festival,

62
00:05:08,833 --> 00:05:13,166
and our numbers
swelled from 7 to 16.

63
00:05:13,250 --> 00:05:17,583
And now? We're a day away
from the Championship.

64
00:05:17,666 --> 00:05:21,208
Think about that. It's so cool.

65
00:05:22,583 --> 00:05:25,041
Guys. I'm glad we
made it this far.

66
00:05:25,125 --> 00:05:27,500
Regardless of
what happens...

67
00:05:29,083 --> 00:05:31,375
[KAZUMA laughs]
Who am I kidding?

68
00:05:31,458 --> 00:05:33,958
I want us to win it all
tomorrow, all right?

69
00:05:34,041 --> 00:05:35,166
Ha!

70
00:05:35,250 --> 00:05:37,708
So, leave everything
out there on the stage.

71
00:05:37,791 --> 00:05:41,083
And let's put on a show
like they've never seen!

72
00:05:41,166 --> 00:05:43,500
Heck yeah! I'm in!

73
00:05:45,625 --> 00:05:47,666
I agree with the Captain.

74
00:05:47,750 --> 00:05:48,416
[TON]
Mm!

75
00:05:48,500 --> 00:05:49,541
You ready, Gen?

76
00:05:49,625 --> 00:05:51,000
I'm ready when you are, dude!

77
00:05:51,083 --> 00:05:52,708
[KAZUMA]
Let's get 'em!

78
00:05:52,791 --> 00:05:58,166
[BREAKERS chattering]

79
00:05:59,875 --> 00:06:02,416
[GIN] You know. It might
be your hair color,

80
00:06:02,500 --> 00:06:04,875
but you don't look
like yourself.

81
00:06:04,958 --> 00:06:07,666
My appearance may have changed,
but I'm still the same guy.

82
00:06:07,750 --> 00:06:10,500
Right. I guess that's
true, but still.

83
00:06:10,583 --> 00:06:15,333
I only dyed it for one reason.
Because I wanted to show off.

84
00:06:15,416 --> 00:06:22,000
I was trying to be unique.
I was trying to be different.

85
00:06:22,083 --> 00:06:26,583
Coach wasn't buyin' it, though.
She saw right through me.

86
00:06:26,666 --> 00:06:28,583
Listen, about what you wrote...

87
00:06:28,666 --> 00:06:31,750
[KIN] Mock my handwriting,
and I'll dye your hair pink!

88
00:06:31,833 --> 00:06:34,166
I'm not making fun of you.

89
00:06:34,250 --> 00:06:36,083
I found it very moving, Kin!

90
00:06:36,166 --> 00:06:37,333
[DOH]
So did I!

91
00:06:37,416 --> 00:06:38,375
[KIN]
Uh?

92
00:06:39,875 --> 00:06:42,208
[KIN] I used to think a man
could only become stronger

93
00:06:42,291 --> 00:06:43,958
by being the bad boy.

94
00:06:44,041 --> 00:06:48,041
But now I see how far from
the truth that really is.

95
00:06:48,125 --> 00:06:51,833
Back then? I was just another
miserable, good-for-nothing jerk

96
00:06:51,916 --> 00:06:55,250
who didn't care about anyone
or anything but himself.

97
00:06:55,333 --> 00:06:58,375
But, Cheerleading
opened my mind.

98
00:06:58,458 --> 00:07:00,750
I learned that a man can
truly become stronger

99
00:07:00,833 --> 00:07:01,750
through hard work.

100
00:07:01,833 --> 00:07:03,625
Through blood, sweat, and tears,

101
00:07:03,708 --> 00:07:06,458
and seeing a task
through to the end.

102
00:07:08,041 --> 00:07:10,250
Can I ask you about
your journal?

103
00:07:10,333 --> 00:07:12,625
Why did you write
so much about me?

104
00:07:12,708 --> 00:07:16,708
Heh, well, uh. It's because
Coach wrote to spoil others

105
00:07:16,791 --> 00:07:20,458
is to spoil yourself, so I put
all my spoiling in one place.

106
00:07:20,541 --> 00:07:25,125
We're family, aren't we? We're
bros. If I'm spoilin' someone,

107
00:07:25,208 --> 00:07:27,875
it might as well be you man.

108
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:33,458
[TAKUMI] Ya know my journal
said the exact same thing

109
00:07:33,541 --> 00:07:34,958
as Gin and Doh's?

110
00:07:35,041 --> 00:07:36,958
Weird, huh?

111
00:07:39,125 --> 00:07:41,625
[GIN] Kin'll be graduating
and leaving the team soon.

112
00:07:41,708 --> 00:07:44,250
And even though it'll be
weird not having him around,

113
00:07:44,333 --> 00:07:46,416
I think we can honor
him by trying our best.

114
00:07:46,500 --> 00:07:48,708
[DOH] I'm thankful I got
to be on the team with him,

115
00:07:48,791 --> 00:07:51,125
and I'm lucky to
call him my friend.

116
00:07:51,208 --> 00:07:53,708
[TAKUMI]
I'll miss Takuya when he's gone.

117
00:07:53,791 --> 00:07:55,416
We did everything together.

118
00:07:55,500 --> 00:07:58,000
Break-dancing, cheering,
competing in tournaments.

119
00:07:58,083 --> 00:08:00,541
Heck, I'll even miss him
worrying about me.

120
00:08:00,625 --> 00:08:03,791
You're the best, bro. I love ya!

121
00:08:05,500 --> 00:08:07,583
Hey, Arale, how goes it?

122
00:08:07,666 --> 00:08:09,208
[ARALE barks]

123
00:08:13,833 --> 00:08:14,958
[HISASHI]
Sorry buddy,

124
00:08:15,041 --> 00:08:17,291
but I gotta leave you
alone tomorrow, too.

125
00:08:17,375 --> 00:08:18,833
[laughs]

126
00:08:18,916 --> 00:08:20,875
You should'a seen
Sho's journal.

127
00:08:20,958 --> 00:08:24,708
He drew a bunch of squirrels
all over the stupid thing.

128
00:08:27,708 --> 00:08:30,833
[HISASHI]
Uh...

129
00:08:30,916 --> 00:08:34,541
As for mine? Let's look.

130
00:08:34,625 --> 00:08:37,541
It says, "Accept that people
are different from you."

131
00:08:37,625 --> 00:08:39,791
Whaddaya think about that, pup?

132
00:08:41,291 --> 00:08:44,916
Guess what?
I actually get it now.

133
00:08:46,083 --> 00:08:48,041
[HISASHI] My reasons for
wanting to do cheerleading

134
00:08:48,125 --> 00:08:49,708
were different than
everyone else's,

135
00:08:49,791 --> 00:08:51,666
and at first, that annoyed me.

136
00:08:51,750 --> 00:08:54,625
But now I realize it's
ultimately a good thing.

137
00:08:54,708 --> 00:08:56,625
Sure, people butt
heads now and then.

138
00:08:56,708 --> 00:09:01,958
But sometimes conflict is the
best way to solve a problem.

139
00:09:02,041 --> 00:09:06,541
And ya'know what? That's part
of what makes team sports fun.

140
00:09:10,208 --> 00:09:12,000
Perfect-o!

141
00:09:12,083 --> 00:09:13,833
[sighs]

142
00:09:18,333 --> 00:09:20,833
[TAKERU] I hope everything
goes well at Nationals.

143
00:09:20,916 --> 00:09:23,625
If I don't pee my pants out
there, then, all things

144
00:09:23,708 --> 00:09:26,916
considered, I'll count
that as a massive victory.

145
00:09:31,625 --> 00:09:35,041
Yeah, yeah, yeah!

146
00:09:35,125 --> 00:09:37,416
"This club is the
worst of all time!

147
00:09:37,500 --> 00:09:40,125
I can't goof off with my friends
and there's no time for fun!

148
00:09:40,208 --> 00:09:44,208
And apart from Ichiro, my
teammates are boring and lame!

149
00:09:44,291 --> 00:09:46,583
Why do I have to put up
with this crap anyway?

150
00:09:46,666 --> 00:09:49,375
All I want from this Club
is to look awesome!

151
00:09:49,458 --> 00:09:52,166
Why the heck are these idiots
falling down all the time?

152
00:09:52,250 --> 00:09:56,458
I can't catch them like that.
It sort of freaks me out!"

153
00:09:56,541 --> 00:09:58,291
Who am I kidding?

154
00:09:58,375 --> 00:10:00,750
When they fall, it totally
freaks me out!

155
00:10:00,833 --> 00:10:01,750
[SAKU]
Yeah, me too.

156
00:10:01,833 --> 00:10:04,166
[TAKERU yelping]

157
00:10:04,250 --> 00:10:07,083
Huh? Why're you here?

158
00:10:07,166 --> 00:10:09,958
I just thought I could use
a brush up rehearsal. You?

159
00:10:10,041 --> 00:10:11,541
[TAKERU]
Don't scare me like that!

160
00:10:11,625 --> 00:10:13,583
[SAKU]
So, it freaks you out, too, huh?

161
00:10:13,666 --> 00:10:15,500
Huh?

162
00:10:15,583 --> 00:10:18,083
I thought I was the only one.

163
00:10:20,208 --> 00:10:21,500
[TAKERU]
"As scared as I am,

164
00:10:21,583 --> 00:10:24,833
it's gotta be a thousand
times worse for the flyers.

165
00:10:24,916 --> 00:10:27,958
Which is why I have to make sure
I catch those guys every time!

166
00:10:28,041 --> 00:10:31,791
They're depending on me!
I can't let them down!"

167
00:10:34,083 --> 00:10:37,875
Ha, ha. I guess I'm a
bit of a drama queen.

168
00:10:37,958 --> 00:10:40,875
Not at all. If I hadn't
read your journal,

169
00:10:40,958 --> 00:10:43,291
I never would've
guessed how you felt.

170
00:10:43,375 --> 00:10:44,958
It was really moving.

171
00:10:45,041 --> 00:10:46,541
Eh, it's no big deal.

172
00:10:46,625 --> 00:10:50,708
If anybody's a big deal, it's
you! Flyin' through the air!

173
00:10:50,791 --> 00:10:54,291
I'm really happy for you, Saku.
You discovered your talent.

174
00:10:54,375 --> 00:10:55,791
[SAKU gasps]

175
00:11:03,791 --> 00:11:06,000
[SAKU]
"I've always felt self-loathing.

176
00:11:06,083 --> 00:11:08,000
I hated how small I was.

177
00:11:08,083 --> 00:11:11,166
How fragile and girlish
I felt like I looked.

178
00:11:11,250 --> 00:11:12,708
But...

179
00:11:12,791 --> 00:11:15,708
Those are the same qualities
that make me an awesome flyer.

180
00:11:15,791 --> 00:11:19,041
Like Kazu, and like Haru, too!"

181
00:11:20,125 --> 00:11:22,375
So, are ya gonna
do it, too, dude?

182
00:11:22,458 --> 00:11:24,541
'Cause I think you
look all pumped up!

183
00:11:24,625 --> 00:11:26,458
Yeah!

184
00:11:27,625 --> 00:11:28,916
[TAKERU]
Double...

185
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:30,666
[BOTH]
...Buh-roccoli!

186
00:11:30,750 --> 00:11:32,541
[BOTH laughing]

187
00:11:32,625 --> 00:11:37,791
Twin Broccoli! A pair
of broccoli! [laughing]

188
00:11:53,541 --> 00:11:55,583
[KAZUMA laughs]

189
00:11:58,208 --> 00:12:01,333
[KAZUMA]
Mom... Dad...

190
00:12:01,416 --> 00:12:03,458
Thanks to you two,
I'm not alone.

191
00:12:03,541 --> 00:12:07,083
I have friends.
They're my teammates.

192
00:12:12,166 --> 00:12:12,958
[HARUKI laughs]

193
00:12:13,041 --> 00:12:13,958
[knocking]

194
00:12:14,041 --> 00:12:15,833
[HARUKO]
Haru, can I come in?

195
00:12:15,916 --> 00:12:17,625
Yeah, sure.

196
00:12:22,250 --> 00:12:23,500
[HARUKO]
Here.

197
00:12:28,208 --> 00:12:29,875
Thank you.

198
00:12:29,958 --> 00:12:32,625
Good luck. I'll cheer for ya.

199
00:12:32,708 --> 00:12:34,208
[HARUKI]
Uh?

200
00:12:34,291 --> 00:12:37,875
Oh. I just thought of this is it
weird to cheer on cheerleaders?

201
00:12:37,958 --> 00:12:41,791
No way. It's not
weird at all, Sis.

202
00:12:43,041 --> 00:12:46,166
That's cheerleading.
Everyone coming together.

203
00:12:46,250 --> 00:12:50,833
Performers and audience. To say,
"let's all do our best today!"

204
00:12:50,916 --> 00:12:52,166
[HARUKO]
Mm.

205
00:13:04,625 --> 00:13:08,541
[BREAKERS chattering]

206
00:13:08,625 --> 00:13:10,125
Gentlemen.

207
00:13:10,208 --> 00:13:12,666
Today we courageously
leap without looking!

208
00:13:12,750 --> 00:13:14,208
That seems a little dangerous!

209
00:13:14,291 --> 00:13:17,041
We will not stop fighting until
justice is achieved for all!

210
00:13:17,125 --> 00:13:18,958
We're not Superheroes,
you know?

211
00:13:19,041 --> 00:13:21,333
[ZI XUAN] Get out there
and break some legs, guys!

212
00:13:21,416 --> 00:13:23,250
[TAKERU]
I'd rather not break anything!

213
00:13:23,333 --> 00:13:24,916
Oh god, it's too much.

214
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:26,291
Somebody please make him stop

215
00:13:26,375 --> 00:13:28,250
before I crash this
bus into a wall.

216
00:13:28,333 --> 00:13:31,375
Zi Xuan sure has come a
long way. I'm proud of him.

217
00:13:31,458 --> 00:13:33,666
Depends on what you
mean by "long way."

218
00:13:33,750 --> 00:13:35,833
[HARUKI, KAZUMA laugh]

219
00:13:43,708 --> 00:13:45,875
Still can't believe we're here.

220
00:13:45,958 --> 00:13:47,291
Yeah.

221
00:13:47,375 --> 00:13:48,875
[DREAMS CAPTAIN 4A]
Coach Takagi!

222
00:13:48,958 --> 00:13:51,875
[TAKAGI] Hi! Did you all
just get here, too?

223
00:13:51,958 --> 00:13:54,250
Yes, we're about to
have a team meeting.

224
00:13:54,333 --> 00:13:55,666
[TAKAGI]
Well, I'm looking forward

225
00:13:55,750 --> 00:13:57,208
to watching your
performance today!

226
00:13:57,291 --> 00:13:58,375
Good luck!

227
00:13:58,458 --> 00:13:59,625
[DREAMS CAPTAIN 4A]
Thank you very much!

228
00:13:59,708 --> 00:14:01,000
We'll see you out there!

229
00:14:01,083 --> 00:14:02,375
[DREAMS]
Later, Coach!

230
00:14:02,458 --> 00:14:03,500
You're cool, right?

231
00:14:03,583 --> 00:14:05,458
Yeah, I'm good.

232
00:14:05,541 --> 00:14:06,208
[gasps]

233
00:14:06,291 --> 00:14:07,875
[HARUKI]
Uh?

234
00:14:12,500 --> 00:14:13,416
Hey!

235
00:14:13,500 --> 00:14:14,875
[CHIHIRO]
Uh...?

236
00:14:14,958 --> 00:14:16,750
Good luck out there!

237
00:14:18,708 --> 00:14:21,333
You too! See ya later!

238
00:14:26,125 --> 00:14:28,875
Haru. All my being weeps
for your broken heart!

239
00:14:28,958 --> 00:14:30,541
Stop it dude, you're
gonna cramp our style.

240
00:14:30,625 --> 00:14:31,750
Get it together!

241
00:14:31,833 --> 00:14:36,375
[CHEERLEADERS chattering]

242
00:14:36,458 --> 00:14:37,791
[KAORU]
Well, speak of the devil.

243
00:14:37,875 --> 00:14:39,583
Hello, Jin.

244
00:14:39,666 --> 00:14:41,541
I was talking, jerk!

245
00:14:41,625 --> 00:14:44,916
Yeah. Sorry. Was it Kyle, or...?

246
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:46,833
It's Kaoru! Kaoru.

247
00:14:46,916 --> 00:14:50,291
I guarantee you're gonna
remember it after today!

248
00:14:50,375 --> 00:14:51,708
Doubtful.

249
00:14:51,791 --> 00:14:53,500
[chuckles]

250
00:14:53,583 --> 00:14:54,791
Uh?

251
00:14:54,875 --> 00:14:57,958
Captain Jin. We look forward
to destroying you!

252
00:14:58,041 --> 00:14:59,916
[TAKERU] Take it easy
with the trash talk, dude!

253
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:03,166
Yeah, hasn't anyone ever told
you not to poke a sleeping bear?

254
00:15:03,250 --> 00:15:05,375
Too late, nerds, because
this sleeping bear's

255
00:15:05,458 --> 00:15:08,333
already awake and he's about
to eat your loser lunch!

256
00:15:08,416 --> 00:15:11,000
I think your mother should've
named you Kao-Rude!

257
00:15:11,083 --> 00:15:14,666
I'd cut that out, Pee-Quan!

258
00:15:14,750 --> 00:15:18,000
You need to hear this.
Our routine's not a circus!

259
00:15:18,083 --> 00:15:18,916
Uh?!

260
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:20,333
[gasps]

261
00:15:20,416 --> 00:15:23,333
Sho wrote that you called us
a circus in his journal.

262
00:15:23,416 --> 00:15:24,916
But if you really believe that,

263
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:26,708
then you don't know
the Breakers at all!

264
00:15:26,791 --> 00:15:28,958
[SHO]
Hey. That's enough, okay?

265
00:15:29,041 --> 00:15:30,708
[ZI XUAN]
No, it's not right, Sho!

266
00:15:30,791 --> 00:15:34,583
You know what Coach
wrote in my journal?

267
00:15:34,666 --> 00:15:36,083
[BOTH]
You brought it with you?!

268
00:15:36,166 --> 00:15:40,833
Check it out.
"Be everyone's teammate!"

269
00:15:40,916 --> 00:15:43,250
I spent a long time
thinking about that.

270
00:15:43,333 --> 00:15:45,958
About what a true
teammate really is.

271
00:15:46,041 --> 00:15:48,541
And then one day it hit
me like a ton of bricks.

272
00:15:48,625 --> 00:15:50,250
And I saw it clearly.

273
00:15:50,333 --> 00:15:54,416
Teammates are the people who
stand up for you no matter what!

274
00:15:59,583 --> 00:16:01,500
Now that was a cool speech.

275
00:16:01,583 --> 00:16:02,625
Yeah, it was.

276
00:16:02,708 --> 00:16:04,166
Let's get out there
today and show 'em

277
00:16:04,250 --> 00:16:05,500
what the Breakers are made of!

278
00:16:05,583 --> 00:16:08,333
We're about to make you
smile till it hurts Jin.

279
00:16:08,416 --> 00:16:10,000
[TON]
Mm.

280
00:16:10,083 --> 00:16:12,458
[SHO gasping]

281
00:16:12,541 --> 00:16:17,708
You know. You're very lucky
to have teammates like them.

282
00:16:21,666 --> 00:16:25,291
[inaudible]

283
00:16:28,916 --> 00:16:30,333
Yeah, you're right.

284
00:16:30,416 --> 00:16:32,416
I think I can finally
show you our routine

285
00:16:32,500 --> 00:16:33,916
with my head held high.

286
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:36,541
Oh yeah? We'll see about that.

287
00:16:36,625 --> 00:16:38,375
Cool headband, said no one.

288
00:16:38,458 --> 00:16:40,291
[KAORU]
It keeps my bangs in place!

289
00:16:40,375 --> 00:16:43,375
[ALL laughing]

290
00:16:43,458 --> 00:16:45,125
[phone chimes]

291
00:16:47,541 --> 00:16:51,291
It's Sakura. She says
she just arrived.

292
00:16:51,375 --> 00:16:52,666
[SHO gasps]

293
00:17:01,125 --> 00:17:03,166
There she is.

294
00:17:09,875 --> 00:17:12,333
Hey, uh. Who's the little kid?

295
00:17:12,416 --> 00:17:13,625
[TAKAGI]
That's my son, Haru.

296
00:17:13,708 --> 00:17:14,791
[BOTH gasping]

297
00:17:14,875 --> 00:17:17,208
He's not a bad looking
guy either, is he?

298
00:17:17,291 --> 00:17:21,583
Coach, wait. Does this mean...

299
00:17:21,666 --> 00:17:24,208
You're a mother. How lovely.

300
00:17:24,291 --> 00:17:25,500
[GIN, DOH]
Uh...

301
00:17:25,583 --> 00:17:27,750
[HARUKI, KAZUMA laugh]

302
00:17:30,916 --> 00:17:32,375
[laughs]

303
00:17:35,041 --> 00:17:36,958
Kirari!

304
00:17:37,041 --> 00:17:38,708
--Woo! Go!
--You can do it, Saku!

305
00:17:38,791 --> 00:17:39,750
You got this!

306
00:17:39,833 --> 00:17:41,375
[SAKU whimpering]

307
00:17:45,333 --> 00:17:49,458
[inaudible]

308
00:17:49,541 --> 00:17:51,541
They're here.

309
00:17:51,625 --> 00:17:53,833
[ANNOUNCER 10A]
And now, ladies and gentlemen,

310
00:17:53,916 --> 00:17:55,791
it's time for the
National Cheerleading

311
00:17:55,875 --> 00:17:58,041
Championship Finals!

312
00:18:05,583 --> 00:18:07,875
How many more groups before us?

313
00:18:07,958 --> 00:18:09,875
I think we're up next, so...

314
00:18:09,958 --> 00:18:13,125
I'm nervous.
Like really nervous.

315
00:18:13,208 --> 00:18:14,625
Yeah, me too.

316
00:18:14,708 --> 00:18:15,625
[TAKUMI grunts]

317
00:18:15,708 --> 00:18:17,125
What's more nerve-wracking, Ton,

318
00:18:17,208 --> 00:18:19,625
going on a hot date or
competing in the Nationals?

319
00:18:19,708 --> 00:18:21,583
I mean like in terms
of performance anxiety,

320
00:18:21,666 --> 00:18:22,500
this is way worse.

321
00:18:22,583 --> 00:18:24,375
[ICHIRO, GEN growling]

322
00:18:24,458 --> 00:18:27,875
Almost time, Breakers!
Right this way, please!

323
00:18:27,958 --> 00:18:29,166
Right!

324
00:18:29,250 --> 00:18:36,416
♪♪♪

325
00:18:45,250 --> 00:18:47,000
[SPARKS]
Go, Sparks!

326
00:18:47,083 --> 00:18:52,625
[CROWD cheering]

327
00:18:52,708 --> 00:18:53,666
[KAZUMA]
Hey, guys.

328
00:18:53,750 --> 00:18:55,250
[ALL gasp]

329
00:18:59,041 --> 00:19:00,291
We got this!

330
00:19:00,375 --> 00:19:01,875
Kazu.

331
00:19:01,958 --> 00:19:03,333
Just remember to smile,

332
00:19:03,416 --> 00:19:06,125
and we'll make 'em
all smile with us!

333
00:19:11,375 --> 00:19:12,750
[ANNOUNCER 10A]
Now onto the next team!

334
00:19:12,833 --> 00:19:14,750
Hailing from
Meiyshiin University,

335
00:19:14,833 --> 00:19:17,541
let's hear it for the Breakers!

336
00:19:17,625 --> 00:19:18,250
[CROWD cheers]

337
00:19:18,333 --> 00:19:20,500
All right! This is it.

338
00:19:20,583 --> 00:19:23,333
[FEMALE ANNOUNCER 10A]
An All-Men's Cheerleading Club,

339
00:19:23,416 --> 00:19:27,416
the Meishiin Breakers formed
just about a year ago.

340
00:19:29,166 --> 00:19:30,666
[BREAKERS]
Go, fight, win!

341
00:19:30,750 --> 00:19:35,625
Let's go... Breakers!

342
00:19:39,541 --> 00:19:41,625
[HARUKI]
Ready!

343
00:19:41,708 --> 00:19:47,166
♪♪♪

344
00:19:53,958 --> 00:19:56,416
[WATARU] I was always
afraid of my true self.

345
00:19:56,500 --> 00:20:00,083
That's why I hid behind
famous quotations.

346
00:20:00,166 --> 00:20:03,000
But now I realize it's
by embracing who we are,

347
00:20:03,083 --> 00:20:05,250
that we can better
understand others.

348
00:20:05,333 --> 00:20:08,791
So I don't hide anymore.
I use my own words now.

349
00:20:08,875 --> 00:20:10,625
And they're awesome.

350
00:20:12,625 --> 00:20:14,250
[ICHIRO]
I was arrogant.

351
00:20:14,333 --> 00:20:17,250
That's what screwed me up during
practice for the festival.

352
00:20:17,333 --> 00:20:19,958
I thought I could be better
than everyone around me.

353
00:20:20,041 --> 00:20:23,125
And that's exactly what
was holding me back.

354
00:20:23,208 --> 00:20:25,083
But now, I'm moving forward.

355
00:20:25,166 --> 00:20:28,166
With open eyes and an open mind.

356
00:20:37,541 --> 00:20:40,375
[GEN] Coach saw what
I needed right away.

357
00:20:42,500 --> 00:20:43,958
[GEN]
Whether it was sports or girls,

358
00:20:44,041 --> 00:20:46,166
I was always comparing
myself to him

359
00:20:46,250 --> 00:20:49,416
instead of worrying
about the team.

360
00:20:49,500 --> 00:20:53,000
But... everyone gets frustrated.

361
00:20:53,083 --> 00:20:56,625
And everyone has things
they're trying to work on!

362
00:21:05,666 --> 00:21:07,500
[GEN]
Before you can help the team,

363
00:21:07,583 --> 00:21:10,625
you have to conquer yourself!

364
00:21:10,708 --> 00:21:12,208
[BREAKERS]
Ha!

365
00:21:14,875 --> 00:21:15,583
[BREAKERS]
Welcome!

366
00:21:15,666 --> 00:21:19,250
B-R-E-A-K-E-R-S!

367
00:21:20,250 --> 00:21:22,250
[BREAKERS]
Go... Breakers!

368
00:21:22,333 --> 00:21:25,125
C'mon, fans! Follow us!

369
00:21:25,208 --> 00:21:27,875
Say black and yellow!

370
00:21:27,958 --> 00:21:31,375
You say black and yellow!


371
00:21:31,458 --> 00:21:34,791
Okay, let's go... Meishiin!


372
00:21:34,875 --> 00:21:38,750
Go for love and... peace!


373
00:21:40,166 --> 00:21:42,500
[inaudible]


374
00:22:06,041 --> 00:22:07,208
[BREAKERS]
Ready!

375
00:22:07,291 --> 00:22:09,000
[TON] I used to criticize
myself constantly.

376
00:22:09,083 --> 00:22:11,625
I'd say, "I can't do this,
it's hopeless."

377
00:22:11,708 --> 00:22:13,708
And I couldn't... Not alone.

378
00:22:13,791 --> 00:22:16,000
But when I had teammates
depending on me.

379
00:22:16,083 --> 00:22:18,166
Supporting me... I learned.

380
00:22:18,250 --> 00:22:21,041
My body is a major
asset for this team.

381
00:22:21,125 --> 00:22:22,833
And when I'm supporting others?

382
00:22:22,916 --> 00:22:25,250
Well, that's when
I'm at my best.

383
00:22:26,958 --> 00:22:28,375
[KAZUMA]
Here's the truth.

384
00:22:28,458 --> 00:22:32,750
Without Haru, I couldn't have
accomplished any of this.

385
00:22:32,833 --> 00:22:37,000
I don't even know if it's
possible to beat him.

386
00:22:37,083 --> 00:22:40,375
But I'm always gonna give
this my all, no matter what.

387
00:22:40,458 --> 00:22:43,708
Because... that's
exactly what Haru does.

388
00:22:43,791 --> 00:22:45,625
[HARUKI]
I can't beat Kazu.

389
00:22:45,708 --> 00:22:49,541
Every time I thought that, it's
like he saw right through me.

390
00:22:49,625 --> 00:22:51,916
He knew what was in my heart.

391
00:22:58,000 --> 00:23:00,791
[HARUKI] But, just like
the rest of this team,


392
00:23:00,875 --> 00:23:03,250
I had to break through it.


393
00:23:03,333 --> 00:23:06,541
After all, it's in the name.


394
00:23:09,416 --> 00:23:13,625
[HARUKI] That's why, from now
on, I wanna beat myself!

395
00:23:13,708 --> 00:23:15,750
[BREAKERS]
Go, Breakers!

396
00:23:15,833 --> 00:23:20,416
[CROWD cheering]

397
00:23:25,333 --> 00:23:29,333
[BREAKERS laughing]

398
00:23:53,625 --> 00:23:55,166
[KAZUMA]
Wanna do something different?

399
00:23:55,250 --> 00:23:58,166
Then join the Men's Cheer Club!

400
00:23:58,250 --> 00:24:00,791
[HARUKI]
Does this look fun to you?

401
00:24:00,875 --> 00:24:05,833
Join the Breakers today, and
let's make some people smile!

402
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:14,333
Go... Fight... Win!

403
00:24:14,416 --> 00:24:18,166
[BREAKERS]
We are... Breakers!

